The
{code:java}
jira:issue_updated
{code}
webhook has empty customfield related with sprint. When we add an issue to a sprint sent webhook contains empty field where should be a sprint value. Changelog contains proper values.

Bug occurs only on Unicorn instances.

h3. Summary
According to the documentation (url below), users should be able to call the /rest/api/2/issue/\{issueIdOrKey}/notify endpoint (see the schema):
- https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/cloud/#api/2/issue-notify

However this only works when sending the username in the request.
 

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Send a request to the notify endpoint using emailAddress like in the below example:
{noformat}
{
    "subject": " eu justo eget augue iaculis fermentum.",
    "textBody": "Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Pellentesque eget venenatis elit. Duis eu justo eget augue iaculis fermentum. Sed semper quam laoreet nisi egestas at posuere augue semper.",
    "htmlBody": "Lorem ipsum <strong>dolor</strong> sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Pellentesque eget venenatis elit. Duis eu justo eget augue iaculis fermentum. Sed semper quam laoreet nisi egestas at posuere augue semper.",
    "to": {
        "users":[
            {
                "emailAddress": "EMAIL_ADDRESS"
            }
        ]
    }
{noformat}


h3. Expected Results
The user correctly receives the notification.

h3. Actual Results 
Error 500 is returned;
{noformat}
{"errorMessages":["Internal server error"],"errors":{}}
{noformat}


h3.Workaround 
Use '{{name}}' instead and pass the username, as the below example:
{noformat}
{
    "subject": " eu justo eget augue iaculis fermentum.",
    "textBody": "Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Pellentesque eget venenatis elit. Duis eu justo eget augue iaculis fermentum. Sed semper quam laoreet nisi egestas at posuere augue semper.",
    "htmlBody": "Lorem ipsum <strong>dolor</strong> sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Pellentesque eget venenatis elit. Duis eu justo eget augue iaculis fermentum. Sed semper quam laoreet nisi egestas at posuere augue semper.",
    "to": {
        "users":[
            {
                "name": "USER_NAME"
            }
        ]
    }
{noformat}

h3. Summary

JQL operators "AND NOT" doesn't work when using "comment"

h3. Steps to Reproduce

# Create a project;
# Create three or more issues;
# Comment on one of the issues, "TEST";
# Go to Search issues;
# Try to search for *project = (Created project) and not comment ~ "TEST"*.

h3. Expected Results

All other issues that are on the project, but not with the comment "TEST".

h3. Actual Results

# Return all issues, even with the comment "TEST";
OR
# Don't return any issues;

h3.Workaround

There is not a workaround to avoid this problem.

Problem Description

Based on  [Webhook documentation|https://developer.atlassian.com/static/connect/docs/latest/modules/common/webhook.html], only the following event types are supported.
 * {{jira:issue_created}}
 * {{jira:issue_deleted}}
 * {{jira:issue_updated}}
 * {{jira:worklog_updated}}

h3. {{Suggested Resolution}}

{{Support other event types for JQL query in Webhook}}

